{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1074d180-362c-4646-b1cd-f95fec6867e7","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues with **two of your three target frameworks**.\n\n**MSTest v3 dropped support for EOL runtimes:**\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET Core side. You'd need to update those TFMs (e.g., to `net6.0` or `net8.0`).\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package.\n- There are also some behavioral breaking changes (e.g., class/assembly cleanup defaults, stricter timeout handling).\n\nTo migrate, you'd update your TFMs and simplify the package references.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6c1c2ce-0721-4324-96e7-3a74738d3ca0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped TFM support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — .NET Core 3.1 is no longer supported (EOL)\n   - `net5.0` — .NET 5.0 is no longer supported (EOL)\n   - For .NET Framework, `net462` and later are supported, so that's fine.\n\nMSTest v3 only targets .NET Framework 4.6.2+, .NET 6.0, and later LTS versions, which means `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` would be incompatible with the upgrade.\n\nThe other major change is that MSTest v3 consolidates everything into a single `MSTest` package rather than separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages, so they'll need to update their dependencies accordingly.","outputTokens":749,"requestId":"5C2E:12F3AB:44DBF7:565926:69F5629F"},"id":"beee1c15-57bd-475d-b771-eef8868705e6","timestamp":"2026-05-